"# Appendix X — Emoji + Easing Cheat-Sheet

The one-page reference. Pin this up. When you don't remember the exact curve or the exact one-liner, come here.

## The named easings, visually

Each easing takes t ∈ [0,1] and returns an eased value in [0,1] (with occasional overshoot). Below is the *shape* of each curve, drawn as a rough ASCII profile — a curve rising from bottom-left (t=0, out=0) to top-right (t=1, out=1). The axis is time going right; the curve's height at each point is the eased output.

```
easing/linear                 easing/ease-in                easing/ease-out
                             .
        .·                 ·                          ·——·
      .·                  ·                         ·
    .·                   ·                        ·
  .·                    ·                       ·
.·                    ·                       ·
                    ·                       ·
                  ·                      .·
                ··                      ·
              ··                      .·
______________          ______________·          _____________

easing/ease-in-out           easing/emphasized             easing/standard
                    ·                          ·                          ·
                  ·                          ·                          ·
                ·                          ·                          ·
              ·                          ·                         ·
            ·                          ·                         ·
          ·                          ·                         ·
        ·                          ·                         ·
      ·                          ·                         ·
    ·                          ·                        ·
  ·                          ·                       ·
··                         ··                      ·
______________          ______________          _____________

easing/decelerated           easing/accelerated            easing/spring
                    ·                          ·                     ·
                  ·                         ·                       · ·
                ·                        ·                        ·   ·  ·
              ·                        ·                        ·     ··
             ·                       ·                        ·        ·
           ·                       ·                        ·          ·
         ·                        ·                       ·
       ·                        ·                       ·
     ·                        ·                       ·
   ·                       ·                       ·
··                       ·                     ·
______________         ______________         _____________
```

Read them as *how the value grows over time*. `linear` grows at constant rate. `ease-in` starts flat and steepens. `ease-out` starts steep and flattens. `spring` overshoots and settles.

## The 11-year-old table — five one-liners

| I want to...          | Type this                                  |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| Make a heart pulse    | `(bounce \"❤️\" :height 15)`               |
| Make text slide in    | `(slide \"HI\" 'left)`                     |
| Make emoji bounce     | `(bounce \"🎉\")`                          |
| Fade in a word        | `(fade \"welcome\")`                       |
| Fade out a toast      | `(fade 'toast :from 1.0 :to 0.0)`          |

Each of these is ONE line of Motoi. Type it, hit run, watch it work. Change the emoji, change the word, change the number.

## The 60-year-old table — five compositions

| I want to...                                    | Compose this                                            |
|-------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Chained physics: springy entrance + dwell + accel exit | `(motion/move-to c x1 y 400 :easing (spring-ease :stiffness 200 :damping 12))` then `(time/when 900 (lambda () (motion/move-to c x2 y 300 :easing easing/accelerated)))` |
| Custom curve matched to a design spec           | `(define house-curve (bezier-ease 0.05 0.7 0.1 1.0))` then `(motion/move-to element x y ms :easing house-curve)` |
| Multi-target orchestration with staggered eases | Iterate a list; `time/when` each element by (i * 80); each `motion/move-to` uses a different easing indexed from a per-role table |
| Fade-in paragraph line by line                  | `(text/wrap s w)` → loop paints each line with `fb/text` and calls `fade` with an incrementing `time/when` delay |
| Score-pop: rise + fade-in + fade-out            | `motion/move-to` (spring), `fade` in for 200ms, `time/when 400` then `fade` out for 200ms, total 600ms |

Each of these is a stack. Each layer is a verb you already know. When the design calls for feel, you build up. When the design calls for get-it-on-screen, you use `bounce`.

## Named-easing recipe cards

### easing/emphasized — for entrances that should command attention
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'hero-title 160 40 500 :easing easing/emphasized)
```

### easing/standard — the safe default
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'panel 200 100 300 :easing easing/standard)
```

### easing/decelerated — soft arrivals
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'toast 20 20 400 :easing easing/decelerated)
```

### easing/accelerated — fast exits
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'notification -100 20 300 :easing easing/accelerated)
```

### easing/linear — clocks, progress bars, marquees
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'clock-hand 200 100 6000 :easing easing/linear)
```

### easing/ease-in — departures with weight
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'ball 300 100 500 :easing easing/ease-in)
```

### easing/ease-out — the classic UI arrival
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'card 200 100 400 :easing easing/ease-out)
```

### easing/ease-in-out — traversals, camera pans
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'camera 300 200 800 :easing easing/ease-in-out)
```

### easing/spring — physical, alive
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'button 100 100 :easing easing/spring)
```

## Emoji one-liner recipes

### Heart pulse
```scheme
(bounce \"❤️\" :height 10 :duration 400)
```

### Confetti burst — three glyphs staggered
```scheme
(bounce \"🎉\")
(time/when 120 (lambda () (bounce \"✨\" :height 30)))
(time/when 240 (lambda () (bounce \"⭐\" :height 25)))
```

### Wave hello
```scheme
(fb/text 100 100 \"👋\")
(entity/rotate! \"👋\" 20 :duration 200 :easing easing/ease-in-out)
(time/when 200 (lambda () (entity/rotate! \"👋\" -20 :duration 200 :easing easing/ease-in-out)))
```

### Slide in from left, dwell, slide out to right
```scheme
(slide \"hello\" 'left :duration 400)
(time/when 400 (lambda ()
  (time/when 800 (lambda ()
    (motion/move-to \"hello\" 400 100 400 :easing easing/accelerated)))))
```

### Fade in title, fade out subtitle
```scheme
(fade \"MOTOI\" :duration 500)
(time/when 500 (lambda () (fade \"press start\" :duration 400)))
```

## Compositions — three lines instead of one

### Bounce + fade — pop and disappear
```scheme
(bounce \"+10\" :height 30 :duration 400)
(time/when 300 (lambda () (fade \"+10\" :from 1.0 :to 0.0 :duration 100)))
```

### Slide + spring — enter with life
```scheme
(motion/move-to 'toast 20 20 :easing (spring-ease :stiffness 180 :damping 12))
(fade 'toast :from 0.0 :to 1.0 :duration 300)
```

### Bounce + rotate — playful attention
```scheme
(bounce \"⭐\" :height 20)
(entity/rotate! \"⭐\" 360 :duration 500 :easing easing/ease-in-out)
```

## Constants at a glance

Fonts (for text):
- `font/default` — proportional, includes emoji
- `font/mono` — monospaced
- `font/big` — large title
- `font/tiny` — dense HUD, tooltip, paragraph

Easings (for motion):
- `easing/emphasized` — attention
- `easing/standard` — default
- `easing/decelerated` — soft entry
- `easing/accelerated` — quick exit
- `easing/linear` — mechanical
- `easing/ease-in` — departure
- `easing/ease-out` — arrival
- `easing/ease-in-out` — symmetric
- `easing/spring` — alive

Primitives (for building your own):
- `bezier-ease` — cubic-bezier(x1, y1, x2, y2)
- `named-ease` — lookup by symbol
- `spring-ease` — physics: stiffness, damping, mass

One-liners (for the fastest path):
- `bounce` — vertical hop
- `slide` — enter from edge
- `fade` — opacity animation

